# Optional TURN relay for WebRTC.
#
# STUN alone covers most direct connections (especially across two different
# devices). A TURN relay is only needed as a fallback when no direct peer path
# exists — restrictive networks, or two tabs on the SAME machine (where browsers
# hide host candidates behind mDNS).
#
# There is no reliable free *zero-config* TURN. To get one:
#   - Free tier: create a key at https://www.metered.ca/tools/openrelay/, or
#   - Self-host coturn (https://github.com/coturn/coturn).
#
# Then copy this file to ".env" and fill in the values below.
# VITE_TURN_URL=turn:your-turn-host:3478
# VITE_TURN_USERNAME=your-username
# VITE_TURN_CREDENTIAL=your-credential
